HEADWORD: Septicidal
<hw>Sep"ti*ci`dal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Septum</ets> + L. <ets>caedere</ets> to cut: cf. F.
<ets>septicide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Dividing the
partitions; -- said of a method of dehiscence in which a pod splits
through the partitions and is divided into its component
carpels.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Septicity</ent>⟦br⟧
